jade.util
Class Logger

java.lang.Object
  jade.util.Logger

public class Logger
extends java.lang.Object

Wrapper class for using the generic Java logging facility which is used by the majority of SPINE core code ex: private static Logger l = Logger.getMyLogger(SPINEManager.class.getName()); if (l.isLoggable(Logger.SEVERE)) l.log(Logger.SEVERE, "Test"); This is maintained in the core SPINE code for compatibility purposes with other platforms Classes that are exclusively Android will usually use the android Catalog Logger ex: Log.i("Test);

Author:
scott.coleman
